{"title": "Short Stories (Later works 1858-65)", "description": "    Elizabeth Gaskell was a regular contributor to Dickens's 'Household Worlds' and 'All The Round' until he later years. From 1858 onwards, she also began to publish in other magazines, including 'Harpers New Monthly Magazine', 'The Cornhill Magazine', 'MacMillan's Magazine', 'Fraser's Magazine for Town and Country', and 'Pall Mall Gazette'. This collection brings together her contributions to these publications from 1858 to 1865, the year of Gaskell's untimely death. It includes a number of short fiction and non-fiction pieces. The stand out of the collection is 'The Doom of the Griffiths', which has appeared in a number of collections of Gaskell's later short fiction. (Summary by Phil Benson)", "duration": 45655, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "4108", "name": " Elizabeth Cleghorn Gaskell"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/shortstories_gaskell_1858-65_2602_librivox/short_stories_later_work2_2602.jpg", "copyright_year": "1858", "genres": ["Single Author Collections"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Phil Benson"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Phil Benson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Annise"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Newgatenovelist"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Uncle Peter 1", "readers": [6097], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shortstories_gaskell_1858-65_2602_librivox/shortstories5_01_gaskell_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3596}, {"section": 2, "title": "Uncle Peter 2", "readers": [6097], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shortstories_gaskell_1858-65_2602_librivox/shortstories5_02_gaskell_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2583}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Doom of the Griffiths 1", "readers": [6097], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/shortstories_gaskell_1858-65_2602_librivox/shortstories5_03_gaskell_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3180}, {"section": 4, "title": "The Doom of the Griffiths 2", "readers": [6097], "path": "htt